arguments.name: Array
arguments.description: The range of data (or pre-defined array) of numeric values within which percent rank is determined.

arguments.name: X
arguments.description: The value for which you want to know the rank within the array.

arguments.name: Significance
arguments.description: A value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage value. If omitted, PERCENTRANK uses three digits (0.xxx).
